<H3> <TI>   Macao To Participate in Hong Kong Global Tourism Fair </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Macao To Participate in Hong Kong Global Tourism Fair </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2405180394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1455 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2405180394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Macao, May 24 (XINHUA) -- The Macao Tourism 
Department and 16 local enterprises including 13 hotels and 
three travel agencies are going to take part in the '94 
International Tourism Fair to be held in Hong Kong from May 26 
to 29. 
  There will be representatives from 52 countries and regions 
worldwide present at the fair. 
  Macao's local band "Tuna Macaense" will perform at the fair 
on May 26 and 27, while representatives from the Macao Tourism 
Department, media organizations, travel agencies and those from 
other countries and regions will attend an evening party -- the 
night of Macao, on the May 27 evening. 
  It will be the ninth time that Macao participates in this 
international tourism fair and it won a best performance award 
in 1993. 
  In recent years, with the fast development of local economy, 
Macao's tourism industry has also developed rapidly. In 1993, 
Macao registered a total of 7.8 million visits by tourists. 

</TEXT>

