<H3> <TI>   Banking Corporation Issues Global Access Credit Card </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Banking Corporation Issues Global Access Credit Card </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2305144394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1309 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2305144394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Macao, May 23 (XINHUA) -- The Hong Kong and Shanghai 
Banking Corporation Macao branch issued today a newly-designed 
Global Access Credit Card which is available in more than 70 
countries worldwide. 
  It is learned that Global Access Credit Card holders can 
draw 
money through more than 160,000 automatic teller machines (ATM) 
scattered over 70 countries in the world. Each time, one holder 
can draw 6,000 Macao patacas or foreign currencies of the same 
value at most. 
  Global Access Card users can transfer accounts, check cash 
surplus, apply for accounts and draw cash in related banks such 
as the Hong Kong and Shanghai Banking Corporation, Banco Hang 
Sang, the Express Net of the Philippines and Hing Kong and 
Shanghai Banking Corporation branch in Canada. 
  The annual charge for global access card stands at 50 Macao 
patacas (about 6.25 U.S. dollars). 

</TEXT>

