<F P=101> Malaysia </F>
<H3> <TI>   * Ministry To Honor Outstanding Scientists </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    * Ministry To Honor Outstanding Scientists </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   11111111 </F>
<F P=103> 11111111 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
CSO 

    [Editorial Report] The Kuala Lumpur UTUSAN MALAYSIA in 
Malay on 20 March, p 2, reported that the government has 
allocated $5 million over a five-year period to establish the 
"Malaysian Science Academy." The academy is to be an "elite" 
organization for "outstanding Malaysian scientists." Science, 
Technology, and Environment Minister Datuk Law Hieng Ding said 
the objective of the organiziation is to foster scientific 
know-how, and to exchange ideas among scientists in analyzing 
national problems and in making recommendations to the 
government. Additionally, Minister Law said, the academy will 
ensure that outstanding scientific contributions, such as new 
inventions, receive due recognition. Scientists who make 
valuable contributions will be called "academicians," and will 
be eligible for a life pension. 

</TEXT>

