<H3> <TI>   Top Leaders Exchange Messages on Peace Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Top Leaders Exchange Messages on Peace Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Sihanouk Asks Khieu Samphan's View </H4>

<F P=102> BK2804153494 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 1300 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2804153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 1300 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Address by King Norodom Sihanouk at palace audience on 28 </F>
April in Phnom Penh -- recorded] 
  [Excerpt] [Partly indistinct passage appealing for the 
release of abducted foreigners] Now I would like to inform 
foreign and local newspapers that the roundtable betwen the 
Royal Government of the Kingdom of Cambodia and Khieu Samphan, 
His Excellency [H.E.] Khieu Samphan, chairman of the Party of 
Democratic Kampuchea, in principle should take place from 2 to 7 
May to find a common means to build and restore a peaceful and 
independent Cambodia with its territorial integrity to avoid 
fighting. Our compatriots have suffered constantly because of 
this war. I would like to ask that this fighting end and to 
have peace and security for our compatriots everywhere 
throughout the Kingdom of Cambodia. 
  Some do not listen to me, to the king. They keep saying that 
they love and respect the king, but in words only not in deeds. 
Therefore, I would like to again beg them to stop fighting and 
turn to talk peacefully to solve the problem. 
  Khieu Samphan, H.E. Khieu Samphan, has said that there is no 
security for him in Phnom Penh. H.E. Hun Sen, Samdech Hun Sen 
and Prince Krompreah Norodom Ranariddh said they can give a 100 
percent guarantee that there will be no danger to H.E. Khieu 
Samphan and other Khmer Rouge members who attend the roundtable 
to talk peacefully. This is 100 percent guaranteed. Despite 
this, H.E. Khieu Samphan and his group do not trust it. They 
want me to take this roundtable to foreign countries instead of 
meeting in our country. The royal government replied that no, 
leaving our country would be a disgrace to our nation, which 
requires that this be held in our country. 
  H.E. Khieu Samphan, please reply to my message, sent to you 
on 24 April. It is already 28 April and H.E. Khieu Samphan has 
not yet replied. Please reply quickly so that I may have enough 
time to organize the roundtable. 
  If he refuses to come to Phnom Penh for the meeting, 
however, 
we will have to postpone it and discuss the matter if this 
cannot be done in Phnom Penh and about the place he wants the 
meeting to be held. In Siem Reap? It seems that he wants to go 
Siem Reap. But I am not sure. Wait until Khieu Samphan writes 
to me and is clear. Since he has not written yet, today I cannot 
inform our compatriots and the foreign and local newspapers. 
So, wait until he answers, then this answer will be 
disseminated. In fact, he wants to meet abroad, China, Korea, 
France, or Indonesia. I do not know. Wait until Khieu Samphan 
writes, then I will inform you. Thank you. [Passage omitted on 
remainder of audience] 

</TEXT>

