<H3> <TI>   Murayama on Election After Budget Passage </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Murayama on Election After Budget Passage </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0105082494 Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN in Japanese 30 Apr 94 
Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0105082494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tomiichi Murayama, chairman of the Social 
Democratic Party of Japan, in an interview with a local TV 
station in Oita City on 29 April, indicated the possibility of 
the House of Representatives being dissolved for a general 
election once the fiscal 1994 budget is passed. He said: "Some 
people say the next election should be held only under the 
single-seat electoral district system. But if there is no 
prospect for finding a breakthrough in the current political 
stalemate, there will be no other choice [but to hold the 
election under the current medium district system]." 

</TEXT>

