<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Quarterly Beef Talks With Australia Begin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Quarterly Beef Talks With Australia Begin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1904032694 Seoul THE KOREA TIMES in English 19 Apr 94 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> SK1904032694 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul THE KOREA TIMES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Korea yesterday entered into a string of quarterly 
bilateral negotiations with Australia, New Zealand and the 
United States to discuss matters concerning Korea's beef imports. 
  The meetings are the third of their kind since a memorandum 
of understanding on beef market access was signed between Korea 
and Korea's three major beef exporters last July, the Ministry 
of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries said. 
  In yesterday's meeting, Australia urged Korea to expand the 
volume of its grass-fed beef sold in wholesale markets to 5,000 
tons from the present 800 tons, said a ministry official who 
attended the meeting. 
  New Zealand is expected to make similar demands in a meeting 
with Korea scheduled for April 25, the official said. 
  The United States with which Korea is scheduled to have a 
beef negotiation April 26 will likely urge Korea to ease 
restrictions on the local distribution of beef. 

</TEXT>

