<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Denounces `Lies' of KR Radio </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Denounces `Lies' of KR Radio </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0305105694 Hong Kong AFP in English 1015 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0305105694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi, May 3 (AFP) -- Vietnam described Tuesday as 
"lies" allegations by the Khmer Rouge [KR] that the Cambodian 
government was attempting to recruit Vietnamese mercenaries to 
fight the guerrillas. 
  "This information is a complete lie," a Vietnamese Foreign 
Ministry spokesman told AFP of a Khmer Rouge radio report on 
Sunday which said government officials had travelled to Vietnam 
"to beg for 20 truckloads of mercenaries to come to the aid of 
defeated government troops in Battambang." 
  Khmer Rouge radio had said government defeats at Anlong Veng 
and Pailin -- guerrilla bases in Cambodia's north and northwest 
taken by government troops but lost again to the Khmer Rouge -- 
had made the recruitment of new soldiers impossible. 
  The guerrilla faction often blames Hanoi for interfering in 
Cambodia, where dozens of ethnic Vietnamese, including women and 
children, have been victims in bloody attacks blamed on the 
Khmer Rouge. 

</TEXT>

