<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 27 KYODO -- The Japan Association of 
Corporate Executives (Keizai Doyukai) on Wednesday [27 April] 
elected as its Vice Chairman Jiro Ushio, chairman of special 
lamp maker Ushio Inc., and Yoshihiko Miyauchi, president of 
leasing firm Orix Corp. 
  The election came at an annual general meeting of the 
leading 
Japanese business organization, officials said. 
  Ushio and Miyauchi replaced Joichi Aoi, chairman of Toshiba 
Corp. and Josei Ito, president of Nippon Life Insurance Co., who 
both retired as vice chief of the organization. 
  The meeting also approved the reappointment as vice chairman 
of Tasuku Takagaki, president of the Bank of Tokyo, Tatsuro 
Toyoda, president of Toyota Motor Corp. and Takashi Imai, 
president of Nippon Steel Corp. 

