<F P=106> [Message from Coprime Ministers Ranariddh and Hun Sen to </F>
King Norodom Sihanouk; dated 3 May] 
  [Text] His Majesty Norodom Sihanouk Varaman, king of the 
Kingdom of Cambodia: 
  Your Majesty, we, the first and second prime ministers of 
the 
Royal Government of Cambodia, having learned of Your Majesty's 
idea concerning a cease-fire and roundtable, beg permission to 
inform Your Majesty of our consent, support, and compliance with 
your lofty idea as follows: 
  1. We will respect and comply with Your Majesty's idea for 
an immediate, complete, and unconditional cease-fire and halt 
between Khmer Royal Armed forces [KRAF] and the Khmer Rouge 
group's armed forces. 
  2. We are ready to send two KRAF generals to take part in 
a cease-fire observation committee to oversee this cease-fire 
throughout Cambodia under Your Majesty's lofty chairmanship. 
  3. We are ready to attend a roundtable meeting under Your 
Majesty's lofty chairmanship after the cease-fire takes effect 
throughout Cambodia and is concretely stabilized. 
  We beg Your Majesty to please accept our most sincere 
fidelity and highest respects. Please forgive any improprieties. 
  [Signed] First Prime Minister Norodom Ranariddh; Second 
Prime 
Minister Hun Sen 
  [Dated] Phnom Penh, 3 May 1994 

