<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Begins Visit to Albania </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Begins Visit to Albania </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0105120594 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0600 
GMT 1 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0105120594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Malaysia and Albania will open new ground in 
bilateral cooperation, including an unprecedented military 
cooperation when Defense Minister Datuk Sri Najib Tun Razak 
began his three-day official visit today to the former communist 
state. Seen as a follow-up to the historic visit by Prime 
Minister Datuk Sri Dr. Mahathir Mohamed last July to the eastern 
European state, Datuk Sri Najib will formally establish military 
ties with Albania under a memorandum of understanding, MOU, to 
be signed the following day. 
  Datuk Sri Najib is flying from Stockholm for the first leg 
of 
his visit to Sweden, Albania, and Croatia when he will meet 
Malaysian troops. He will also establish closer rapport and 
Islamic cooperation with his majority Muslim states. 
  Albania has 3.3 million people, more than 80 percent of them 
Muslims. According to the minister's press secretary Zulkifli 
Ali, Datuk Sri Najib will hold a dialogue session tomorrow with 
Albanian religious leaders in a Tirana mosque, built in 1793 
situated in the heart of the state capital. Like previous 
official visits by Malaysian leaders, Datuk Sri Najib is also 
expected to take the opportunity from his stay to explore 
business opportunities for Malaysians to venture in the 
redevelopment process of Albania. 

</TEXT>

