<F P=100> Brunei, Malaysia &amp; Singapore </F>
<F P=101> Singapore </F>
<H3> <TI>   External Trade Recorded `Strong Growth' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    External Trade Recorded `Strong Growth' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2904031294 Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation in 
English 1100 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2904031294 </F>
<F P=104>  Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Currency in Singapore dollars] </F>
  [Text] Singapore registered strong growth in external trade 
last month. The volume grew more than 13 percent on a 
three-month moving average basis. The value of the total trade 
jumped about 11 percent to 24 billion dollars. Import volume 
also rose 11 percent to over 12 billion dollars. Non-oil 
exports saw a 17 percent rise in volume as shipments to both the 
U.S. and Japan recorded rises. Deliveries to the U.S. were up 
13.5 percent and a surge of 24.7 percent to Japan. This growth 
was largely in integrated circuits, computers, and computer 
peripherals. But non-oil exports to the EC dipped 2.9 percent. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

