<H3> <TI>   Commentary Views ROK Hwarang Military Exercise </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commentary Views ROK Hwarang Military Exercise </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0305071594 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1220 GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0305071594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1220 GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Commentary by Yun Pyong-son: "Bellicose Nature Cannot be </F>
Concealed"] 
  [Text] The Kim Yong-sam puppet clique frantically staged 
the so-called Hwarang war exercise in Inchon and the areas of 
Kyonggi Province during 25-29 April. 
  The puppets are now raving that this war was aimed at 
countering someone's infiltration and enhancing defense 
preparedness. However, this is nothing but a sophism to mislead 
the media at home and abroad and to conceal their bellicose 
nature. 
  The entire world officially recognizes that there is no such 
threat of a southward invasion on the Korean peninsula. Even 
though the puppets are raising a clamor as though we would at 
once invade the South, many patriotic figures who have visited 
the Northern half of the Republic unanimously say that there was 
no such moves, and that they have not detected any of those 
moves, and that North Korean society is in peace. 
  Not long ago, traitor Kim Yong-sam himself virtually denied 
the rumors on the threat of a southward invasion by saying that 
the rumors on the war crisis on the Korean peninsula stemmed 
from the U.S. media's irresponsible reports. This vividly 
proves the absurdity of the rumors on the threat of a southward 
invasion babbled by the puppets. 
  There is no such southward invasion but a northward invasion 
on the Korean peninsula. This can be clearly seen in the 
content of operations and the massive number of personnel that 
were mobilized in staging the recent exercise. 
  In the recent Hwarang exercise, the Kim Yong-sam clique 
mobilized the puppet army, navy, and air force and police, and 
reserve forces -- over 1.3 million in all -- and perpetrated a 
surprise mobilization exercise, a joint operation among Army, 
Navy, and Air force, an airborne-operation, and a land operation 
in an atmosphere of real warfare. What is more, they are 
bluffing of a war-winning posture in the event of the firm 
establishment of an emergency situation. 
  Denial of rumors on the war crisis while staging the Hwarang 
war exercise and babbling about the firmness of war-winning 
posture, clearly show that such war an exercise is part of their 
maneuvers to provoke a war of aggression against the North. 
  As a matter of fact, it is an established fact that the 
South 
Korean puppets are attempting to provoke a war of aggression 
against the North with the U.S. imperialists. 
  The U.S. imperialists, on the pretext of stopping the 
North's 
nuclear development, have not withdrawn their naval armed forces 
concentrated on the waters of the Korean peninsula. Worse 
still, they say they are ready for war and are massively 
introducing combat equipment, including the latest-type Patriot 
missiles and Apache attack helicopters into South Korea. 
  In the meantime, the South Korean puppets, along with the 
U.S. imperialists, have mapped out a northward invasion plan 
called the New Operation Plan 5027 and are playing with fire to 
carry it into practice. 
  The U.S. imperialists have perpetrated aerial espionage on 
the northern half of Korea on 250 occasions in April alone. 
This clearly shows how desperately the rascals are running 
about in their maneuvers for a war of aggression against the 
North. 
  Timed to coincide with this, the Kim Yong-sam clique staged 
the Hwarang exercise by mobilizing the puppet army, police, and 
reservists. It is obvious that the Hwarang war exercise is 
aimed at provoking a war of aggression against the North to 
drive not only the puppet army but also the para-military forces 
and inhabitants into it. The puppet clique cannot by any means 
conceal its bellicose nature, and only runs out to the road of 
confrontation and war. 
  The Kim Yong-sam clique's criminal acts of rejecting the 
fellow countrymen's proposal on convening a great national 
meeting; turning the Korean peninsula into a war ground; 
becoming a vanguard of implementing the U.S. policies of 
invasion and war; and bringing in the fiery cloud of war on the 
Korean peninsula will never be tolerated. 
  We (?want dialogue), but we are not in any sense afraid of 
war. If the puppets set the fire of war on this land, our people 
and our People's Army will rise as one to provide the rascals 
with ignominious defeat. 
  The Kim Yong-sam puppet clique should look squarely at the 
unshakable will of our people who do not say empty words, and 
should not act recklessly like a puppy with no fear of a tiger. 

</TEXT>

