<H3> <TI>   `Hostile Acts' Against Korean Residents in Japan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Hostile Acts' Against Korean Residents in Japan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0105084994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0821 GMT 1 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0105084994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Prompt Halt to Anti-Chongnyon Moves Urged" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, May 1 (KCNA) -- Papers here today say the 
recent grave hostile acts against organizations of the General 
Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) and Koreans 
in Japan are unprecedented since the formation of Chongnyon and 
they are premeditated and organized provocations of the Japanese 
reactionaries who have resorted to anti-DPRK, anti-Chongnyon 
moves, motivated by a sinister political aim. 
  A NODONG SINMUN analyst says: 
  Very ill-boding is the situation today when the Japanese 
reactionaries are intensifying crackdown on and persecution of 
Chongnyon and Koreans in Japan. 
  Koreans in Japan are those who were forcibly taken to Japan 
by the Japanese imperialists during their colonial rule, and 
their descendents, and Chongnyon is a patriotic and democratic 
organization of citizens overseas of the DPRK. 
  It is a legal and moral obligation of the Japanese 
authorities to guarantee legitimate activities of Chongnyon and 
the democratic national rights of Koreans in Japan. 
  Nevertheless, the Japanese authorities forcibly searched 
Chongnyon organizations by invoking government power on charges 
of "forcible obstruction of business" which had nothing to do 
with Chongnyon and goaded a rightwing gangsters' group on to 
undisguised suppression and provocations against Chongnyon and 
Koreans in Japan. This is an unjustifiable, rude behavior. 
  We who regard the dignity of our country and nation as our 
life and soul will consider any crackdown on Chongnyon and its 
affiliated organizations and Koreans in Japan an encroachment on 
the dignity and sovereignty of our Republic and decisively 
counter it. 
  The Japanese authorities should ponder over unpredictable 
grave consequences to be entailed by their reckless behavior and 
immediately renounce their policy hostile to the DPRK and 
anti-Chongnyon moves. 

</TEXT>

