<H3> <TI>   Foreign Media Notes Kim Il-song's Birthday </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Media Notes Kim Il-song's Birthday </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0205104494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1026 GMT 2 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0205104494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- Foreign mass media gave 
special write-ups on the occasion of the birthday of the great 
leader President Kim Il-song. 
  The Pakistan paper NIDAE WAQT April 15 gave special 
write-ups 
with a portrait of President Kim Il-song. 
  The paper edited articles titled "Kim Il-song, the Great 
Sun" 
and "Warm Congratulations to His Excellency President Kim 
Il-song, the Great Leader of the Korean People, on His 82nd 
Birthday." 
  It wrote in the preface: 
  Today the Korean people and the world people are grandly 
celebrating the birthday of President Kim Il-song as a common 
auspicious fete of mankind. President Kim Il-song has turned 
Korea into a powerful socialist country independent in politics, 
self- sustaining in the economy and self- reliant in national 
defence in a short historical period, and a people's paradise. 
  He enjoys boundless respect and reverence of the Korean 
people and the world revolutionary people as the most 
outstanding leader of the working class for his immortal feats 
and contributions to the Korean revolution and the world 
revolution. 
  The Tanzanian paper MFANYA KAZI, the Yemeni paper AS-RAI 
AL-AAM, the Nepalese paper MAJADUR KISSAN, the Guyanese paper 
NEW NATION and the Ugandan paper THE NEW VISION gave special 
write-ups. 
  The Exito Radio of Peru, a radio of Equatorial Guinea, the 
Kilikya TV of Lebanon organized congratulatory programs on his 
birthday. 
  The French Committee to Support the Founding of the 
Democratic Confederal Republic of Koryo, the Algeria-Korea 
Friendship Club, the Guyana-Korea Friendship Association, the 
Zimbabwe-Korea Solidarity and Friendship Association and the 
Burundi-Korea Friendship Association issued bulletins on the 
occasion of the April 15 fete. 

</TEXT>

