<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anniversary of `Famous' Kim Il-song Work Marked </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anniversary of `Famous' Kim Il-song Work Marked </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0305054394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0434 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0305054394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 3 (KCNA) -- A symposium was held in 
Pyongyang on May 2 to commemorate the 20th anniversary of the 
publication of "On Some Tasks For Improving Education in 
Schools", a famous work of the great leader President Kim 
Il-song, on May 3, 1974. 
  Speeches were made under the subjects "The great leader 
Comrade Kim Il-song's famous work 'On Some Tasks for Improving 
Education in Schools' is a highly important work indicating the 
way of developing education in schools to a new, higher stage in 
keeping with the requirements of modelling the whole society on 
the chuche idea" and "The idea of enhancing the sense of 
responsibility and role of instructors of the League of 
Socialist Working Youth of Korea and the Children's Union at 
schools is a great idea giving sure guarantee for bringing up 
students to be revolutionaries boundlessly loyal to the party 
and the leader". 
  The speakers said the work of President Kim Il-song is a 
great ideological and theoretical weapon which gives 
comprehensive answers to theoretical and practical questions 
arising in developing education in schools to a new, higher 
stage in conformity with the requirements of modelling the whole 
of society on the chuche idea. 
  With the exposition of the idea of combining education with 
organisational life in the socialist society by the great 
leader, a firm guarantee has been provided for rearing the youth 
and children to be staunch revolutionaries with perfect 
ideological and mental traits as communists of chuche type, the 
speakers stressed. 
  They pointed out that the work indicates the matters of 
thoroughly establishing the party's monolithic ideological 
system among the teachers in keeping with the requirements of 
modelling the whole society on the chuche idea, improving their 
quality and bringing home to them how to educate students. 
  Elaborating on the remarkable achievements made in the 
education in schools over the past 20 years, they said that all 
the educators must further strengthen and develop the education 
at schools and make an active contribution to the accomplishment 
of the cause of socialism, the revolutionary cause of chuche. 
  The meeting was attended by Choe Tae-pok, alternate 
Politburo 
member and secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' 
Party of Korea. 

</TEXT>

