<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   May Day Celebrations, Activities Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    May Day Celebrations, Activities Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    National Celebration Detailed </H4>

<F P=102> SK0205051994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0504 GMT 2 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0205051994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- Workers and other 
laboring masses of Korea significantly celebrated May Day, the 
international holiday of the world working class. 
  Premier Kang Song-san, Vice Presidents Yi Chong-ok and Pak 
Song- chol and other party and government cadres went to 
industrial establishments Sunday to enjoy the holiday together 
with workers. 
  At factories and enterprises, including the Komdok general 
mining enterprise, the Namgang power station, the Kim Chaek iron 
and steel complex, the Pyongyang textile combine, the Hungnam 
fertilizer complex and Nampo Port, they congratulated workers on 
the new upsurge they were bringing about in the implementation 
of the party's revolutionary economic strategy, and enjoyed the 
holiday, mixed with them, while appreciating art performance, 
dancing and holding colorful events. 
  The party and government cadres saw round products newly 
manufactured by Korean workers, conversed with labor innovators 
and paid visits to workers' houses. They expressed the belief 
that workers would always stamsocialism centred on the masses 
and strengthen solidarity with the workers in other countries. 
  On the same day, artistes of central art troupes gave 
performances in parks and pleasure grounds in the capital city 
of Pyongyang. 

</TEXT>

