<H3> <TI>   GM Division To Join Toyota-Affiliated Group </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    GM Division To Join Toyota-Affiliated Group </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2704105394 Tokyo KYODO in English 1002 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2704105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nagoya, April 27 KYODO -- A group of auto parts 
makers affiliated with Toyota Motor Corp. said Wednesday [27 
April] it will accept parts operations of General Motors Japan 
Ltd. as its members. 
  The group consists of auto parts makers in Tokyo, Osaka and 
Nagoya regions. 
  Joining the group are parts and power divisions of the 
Japanese subsidiary of the major U.S. automaker and electronic 
control makers affiliated with them, the organization said. 
  They are the first members affiliated with the major U.S. 
automaker although four automotive firms have already joined the 
group, the organization said. 

</TEXT>

