<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IAEA Informs DPRK of Decision Not To Send Inspectors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0205225994 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 2200 GMT 2 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0205225994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [AFP/YONHAP from Vienna] </F>
  [Text] The International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA] 
announced today that it will not send its inspection team to 
observe the changing of nuclear fuel rods at North Korea's 
nuclear reactor in Yonbyon for the time being since North Korea 
has rejected conditions set to inspect its nuclear facilities. 
IAEA spokesman Hans Meyer disclosed that the IAEA sent a notice 
on 1 May that the IAEA will not be sending its inspection team 
due to North Korea's unsatisfactory responses. 

</TEXT>

